      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Half length shot in an oval frame, depicting a man in an Orthodox priest's vestment, adorned with insignias of honour.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Kliment Tarnovski (born Vasil Nikolov Drumev (~ 1840 – 1901), known by his title as Metropolitan Kliment of Tarnovo, was a leading Bulgarian clergyman and politician. He was also a writer and among the founders of the Bulgarian Literary Society in 1869 in Braila, the Kingdom of Romania.</ab>
